\begin_layout Chapter
Conclusion And Future Work
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
During the past decade, there has been a great interest in RFID due to the
 vast array of applications used in this field.
 RFID systems provide low cost and low power object identification and tracking
 mechanisms, being the key requirement for anticipated ultra dense applications,
 e.g., Logistics.
 In such applications, dense number of tags are expected.
 Furthermore, the number of tags are unknown.
 Thus, the most suitable standard for such applications is the EPCglobal
 C1 G2.
 This standard uses UHF frequency range and passive tags, which gives the
 advantage of having cheap identification process and 
